1
00:00:12,913 --> 00:00:15,714
AT LEAST JAROD COULD HAVE LED US
TO A PLACE NEAR THE STRIP,

2
00:00:15,783 --> 00:00:17,716
THEN I COULD HAVE
HIT THE CRAPS TABLE.

3
00:00:17,785 --> 00:00:21,553
[ Clears Throat ]
WELL, HIT THIS INSTEAD:
SINGLE MALT, LIKE YOU ASKED FOR.

4
00:00:21,622 --> 00:00:24,389
AND YOU'RE FORGETTING SOMETHING.
JAROD DIDN'T LEAD US HERE.

5
00:00:24,458 --> 00:00:27,492
<i>HIS FRIEND TOLD HIM</i>
<i>TO STAY HERE IN AN E-MAIL</i>
<i>I INTERCEPTED.</i>

6
00:00:27,561 --> 00:00:32,331
HE'S BEEN COMPROMISED THIS TIME,
AND HE'S GONNA WALK RIGHT INTO
OUR HANDS.
<i> MY</i> HANDS.

7
00:00:32,399 --> 00:00:37,102
NOW GO TO YOUR ROOM.
OH, THIS IS MY ROOM. OUR ROOM.
THIS IS THE HONEYMOON SUITE.

8
00:00:37,171 --> 00:00:40,905
NOT EVEN AFTER FOUR OF THESE.
OH, NO, NO. MISS PARKER,
IT'S PERFECT.

9
00:00:40,974 --> 00:00:44,509
WHY DO YOU THINK SYDNEY AND
LYLE ARE COMING TOMORROW?
IF JAROD CAME HERE...

10
00:00:44,578 --> 00:00:48,346
AND HE SAW A WOMAN AND THREE MEN
ON THE REGISTER, WELL, HE'D--
HE'D KNOW WE'RE HERE.

11
00:00:48,415 --> 00:00:50,582
THIS WAY, IF--
IF YOU AND I PRETEND...

12
00:00:50,650 --> 00:00:53,252
TO BE THE HONEYMOON COUPLE,
WELL, HE'D BE NONE THE WISER.

13
00:00:55,655 --> 00:00:58,690
- THIS WAS YOUR IDEA.
- YEAH.

14
00:00:58,759 --> 00:01:01,759
<i>I MEAN, IT'S A GOOD ONE,</i>
<i>ISN'T IT? NOBODY'D</i>
<i>BELIEVE YOU AND SYD.</i>

15
00:01:01,829 --> 00:01:04,196
HE'S-- HE'S MIDDLE-AGED,
AND HE'S FLEMISH.

16
00:01:04,264 --> 00:01:08,466
<i>AND YOU, YOU'RE YOUNG AND--</i>
<i>UNLESS YOU THINK THAT YOU'D</i>
<i>RATHER ROOM WITH LYLE.</i>

17
00:01:08,536 --> 00:01:11,036
<i>CENTRE'S A SICK PLACE BUT--</i>
<i>BUT YOUR OWN BROTHER?</i>

18
00:01:13,173 --> 00:01:15,541
RELAX, ROMEO.
THAT'S AS FAR AS I GO.

19
00:01:15,609 --> 00:01:18,811
TAKE FIRST WATCH. ANYBODY
PULLS INTO THAT PARKING LOT,
SEND UP A FLARE.

20
00:01:18,879 --> 00:01:20,945
OKAY.
<i> BROOTS?</i>

21
00:01:21,014 --> 00:01:23,548
<i> FALL ASLEEP, IT'LL BE</i>
<i> A HELL OF A WEDDING NIGHT.</i>

22
00:01:34,828 --> 00:01:36,828
[ No Audible Music ]

23
00:01:43,671 --> 00:01:46,672
<i>[ Bird Chirping In Distance ]</i>

24
00:01:48,241 --> 00:01:50,241
[ Sighs ]

25
00:01:55,316 --> 00:01:58,550
[ Murmurs,
Clears Throat ]

26
00:02:11,931 --> 00:02:14,866
- [ Gasps ]
- [ Sighs ]

27
00:02:14,935 --> 00:02:17,835
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>WELCOME TO SIN CITY--</i>
<i>LAS VEGAS, NEVADA.</i>

28
00:02:17,904 --> 00:02:21,940
<i>A PRETENDER COULD WIN BIG HERE--</i>
<i>SOME OTHER PRETENDER.</i>

29
00:02:22,009 --> 00:02:24,643
<i>I'VE BEEN ROLLING NOTHING</i>
<i>BUT SNAKE EYES.</i>

30
00:02:24,711 --> 00:02:28,980
<i>I SHOULD BE HAVING SOME FUN</i>
<i>IN THE SUN, AND ALL I GOT IS...</i>
<i>FROSTBITE.</i>

31
00:02:29,049 --> 00:02:32,350
<i>THEY SAY LUCK IS A LADY.</i>
<i>THAT MUST BE GOOD LUCK.</i>
[ Shivering ]

32
00:02:32,419 --> 00:02:36,187
-<i> BAD LUCK IS DEFINITELY A MAN,</i>
<i>  AND HE DRESSES FUNNY.</i>
- [ Teeth Chattering ]

33
00:02:36,256 --> 00:02:39,324
<i>ARGYLE TRIED</i>
<i>TO SELL ME TO THE CENTRE</i>
<i>A COUPLE OF YEARS BACK.</i>

34
00:02:39,393 --> 00:02:41,326
<i>LAST YEAR HE ALMOST</i>
<i>GOT ME KILLED.</i>

35
00:02:41,395 --> 00:02:44,162
- [ Sneezes ]
-<i> WHY SHOULD THIS YEAR</i>
<i> BE ANY DIFFERENT?</i>

36
00:02:44,231 --> 00:02:47,199
- [ Whimpers ]
-<i> SOME DAYS IT DOESN'T PAY</i>
<i> TO ANSWER YOUR E-MAIL.</i>

37
00:02:48,535 --> 00:02:51,670
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

38
00:02:51,739 --> 00:02:53,671
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

39
00:02:53,740 --> 00:02:57,308
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

40
00:02:57,377 --> 00:03:00,779
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

41
00:03:00,848 --> 00:03:04,282
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

42
00:03:04,351 --> 00:03:06,551
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

43
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:09,387
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

44
00:03:09,456 --> 00:03:12,190
-<i> THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.</i>
- PREFERABLY.

45
00:03:12,259 --> 00:03:15,193
<i>- [ Miss Parker ] HE DEFENDS</i>
<i>  THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>
<i>- [ Jarod ] LIFE'S A GIFT.</i>

46
00:03:26,974 --> 00:03:29,440
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

47
00:03:36,082 --> 00:03:38,783
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>LOOK AT ME. SOME GENIUS.</i>

48
00:03:38,852 --> 00:03:41,620
<i>I WISH I COULD PRETEND MYSELF</i>
<i>INTO SOME LONG JOHNS.</i>

49
00:03:41,688 --> 00:03:46,958
<i>BUT IN MY OWN DEFENSE,</i>
<i>THIS ALL STARTED WHEN ARGYLE</i>
<i>DECIDED TO BECOME A PRETENDER.</i>

50
00:03:47,027 --> 00:03:50,595
<i>AS USUAL, HIS MOUTH</i>
<i>WAS WRITING CHECKS</i>
<i>HIS BRAIN COULDN'T CASH.</i>

51
00:03:52,632 --> 00:03:54,566
HELLO?

52
00:03:56,302 --> 00:03:58,236
HELLO?

53
00:03:59,973 --> 00:04:02,574
HA! PREPARE TO DIE,
YOU MAMALUKE. OW! OOH!

54
00:04:02,643 --> 00:04:05,543
AH! HEY! HEY!
[ Grunts ]

55
00:04:05,612 --> 00:04:08,112
- J-MAN! YOU MADE IT.
- ARGYLE, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

56
00:04:08,181 --> 00:04:12,717
I'M SORRY, J-DOG.
YOU SAW THE DOOR.
THIS IS A DANGEROUS BUSINESS.

57
00:04:13,953 --> 00:04:15,887
AND WHEN YOU'RE THE MAC DADDY
OF PRIVATE DICKS,

58
00:04:15,955 --> 00:04:19,390
THE FLYIN' MONKEYS--
ALL THEY WANNA DO IS PUT YOU ON
THE NIGHT TRAIN TO EMERALD CITY.

59
00:04:19,459 --> 00:04:23,895
YOU'RE LUCKY YOU DIDN'T GET YOUR
TICKET PUNCHED, RICHARD DIXON,
PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR.

60
00:04:23,964 --> 00:04:27,231
-<i> OH, NO. I AIN'T DICK DIXON.</i>
<i>  I'M HIS PARTNER.</i>
<i>- SO WHY DID YOU E-MAIL ME?</i>

61
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:29,267
WHY DON'T YOU GET HIM
TO HELP YOU?

62
00:04:29,336 --> 00:04:31,903
OH. WELL, YOU SEE,
THIS AIN'T DOUBLE "D'S"
KIND OF GIG.

63
00:04:31,972 --> 00:04:35,640
<i>THIS IS WHAT WE</i>
<i>IN THE INDUSTRY CALL</i>
<i>A "MULTIFACETAL" TYPE THING.</i>

64
00:04:35,709 --> 00:04:38,610
<i>SEE, THERE'S A LOT</i>
<i>OF CROSS-PURPOSING ENTITIES,</i>
<i>MULTICULTURAL...</i>

65
00:04:38,679 --> 00:04:40,979
PURPOSES, YOU KNOW--
ALL OF THAT AND WHATNOT.

66
00:04:41,048 --> 00:04:44,382
- GOOD-BYE, ARGYLE.
- NO, NO, NO! WAIT! J-DOG.
J-DOG. YOU CAN'T LEAVE ME.

67
00:04:44,451 --> 00:04:49,454
YOU CAN'T LEAVE.
YOU'RE ALL I GOT, MAN.
I'M IN TROUBLE, JAROD. PLEASE.

68
00:04:49,523 --> 00:04:53,925
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>RAYMOND CHANDLER HAD A SECRET</i>
<i>FOR WRITING DETECTIVE STORIES.</i>

69
00:04:53,994 --> 00:04:57,495
<i>"WHEN IN DOUBT," HE SAID,</i>
<i>"HAVE SOMEBODY ENTER THE ROOM</i>
<i> WITH A GUN."</i>

70
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:02,434
<i>OKAY, IT'S AN ICE-CREAM CONE.</i>
<i>BUT IT WAS PISTACHIO,</i>

71
00:05:02,503 --> 00:05:04,903
<i>AND I'M ALLERGIC TO PISTACHIOS.</i>

72
00:05:04,971 --> 00:05:09,507
- YOU DICK DIXON?
- ME? NO. I'M HIS PARTNER.
THAT'S DICK DIXON.

73
00:05:11,345 --> 00:05:15,013
- OH! OW!
- THINK THAT HURT?
TASTE THIS.

74
00:05:15,081 --> 00:05:17,449
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>LET'S CALL THIS STORY</i>
<i>"DEATH BY DOUBLE DIP."</i>

75
00:05:17,518 --> 00:05:19,851
<i>NOW, OUR PISTACHIO-PACKING</i>
<i>FRIEND WILL HAVE TO WAIT,</i>

76
00:05:19,919 --> 00:05:23,054
<i>SINCE THE PRETENDER</i>
<i>IS NOW DICK DIXON, PRIVATE EYE.</i>

77
00:05:23,123 --> 00:05:26,958
<i>LET ME GIVE YOU THE SKINNY.</i>
<i>ARGYLE'S NEW JOB WAS ANOTHER</i>
<i>EPIC WORK OF FICTION.</i>

78
00:05:27,027 --> 00:05:29,694
<i>DICK DIXON</i>
<i>ISN'T EVEN AROUND ANYMORE.</i>

79
00:05:29,763 --> 00:05:32,397
<i>HE SKIPPED TOWN LAST YEAR</i>
<i>BURIED IN DEBT.</i>

80
00:05:32,465 --> 00:05:35,167
<i>ARGYLE HAD ONLY BECOME</i>
<i>HIS PARTNER A WEEK EARLIER.</i>

81
00:05:35,235 --> 00:05:38,136
<i>HE WAS WORKING THE BUILDING</i>
<i>AS A "HOSPITALITY TECHNICIAN."</i>

82
00:05:38,205 --> 00:05:41,639
<i>AND THAT'S WHAT HE CALLED IT.</i>
<i>I CALL IT "JANITOR."</i>

83
00:05:41,708 --> 00:05:46,678
<i>HE HAPPENED TO BE SCRUBBING</i>
<i>DICK DIXON'S ABANDONED OFFICE</i>
<i>WHEN... SHE WALKED IN.</i>

84
00:05:46,747 --> 00:05:48,679
I'M LOOKING FOR DICK?

85
00:05:50,717 --> 00:05:52,717
EXCUSE ME?

86
00:05:54,621 --> 00:05:57,355
- YOU KNOW-- DICK.
- DICK?

87
00:05:57,424 --> 00:06:01,659
- DICK DIXON?
- OH. OH. DICK DIXON.

88
00:06:01,728 --> 00:06:05,196
UH, YEAH.
UM, NO. HE'S GONE.

89
00:06:05,265 --> 00:06:07,465
- GONE?
- YEAH. HE TOOK
THE SLOW BOAT TO CHINA.

90
00:06:07,534 --> 00:06:09,534
WASTIN' AWAY IN MARGARITAVILLE--
THAT KIND OF THING.

91
00:06:09,602 --> 00:06:11,636
- DO YOU WORK FOR HIM?
- DO I WORK FOR HIM?

92
00:06:11,705 --> 00:06:15,873
- YEAH.
- DO I WORK FOR HIM?
I AM HIS NOM DE PLUME.

93
00:06:15,942 --> 00:06:19,043
<i> I'M HIS COUP DE GRÂCE.</i>
<i> I AM HIS COMRADE-IN-ARMS,</i>
<i> YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYIN'?</i>

94
00:06:19,112 --> 00:06:23,548
-<i> I AM HIS PARTNER,</i>
<i>  FOR PETE'S SAKE.</i>
- UM, YOU DO HIS DIRTY WORK?

95
00:06:23,617 --> 00:06:26,985
THAT'S FUNNY.
THIS MOP-- YOU SEE--
I'M UNDERCOVER.

96
00:06:27,054 --> 00:06:30,421
I'M WHAT WE IN THE INDUSTRY CALL
THE "CLANDESTINAL" PARTNER.

97
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:33,258
WHATEVER DICK WANTS,
ARGYLE GETS DICK.

98
00:06:33,326 --> 00:06:36,061
<i>"ARGYLE."</i>
<i>THAT'S AN INTERESTING NAME.</i>

99
00:06:36,130 --> 00:06:38,830
YEAH. MY PARENTS GAVE IT TO ME
ON ACCOUNT OF MY BIRTHMARK.

100
00:06:38,898 --> 00:06:41,767
HEY, WOULD YOU LIKE
TO SEE MY BIRTHMARK?

101
00:06:41,835 --> 00:06:45,003
- NO.
- OH, NO. I'M SORRY. I--

102
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:48,506
- [ Sobs ]
- I GET THAT A LOT. PLEASE DON'T
CRY. I HATE TO SEE A GIRL CRY.

103
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:53,111
HERE. TAKE THIS.
THERE YOU GO.
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

104
00:06:53,179 --> 00:06:55,546
- SAY, WHAT'S YOUR NAME?
- MONA.

105
00:06:55,615 --> 00:06:58,549
- LIKE THE LISA?
- YEAH.

106
00:06:58,618 --> 00:07:01,586
- THAT'S VERY BEAUTIFUL.
- [ Blows Nose Loudly ]

107
00:07:02,822 --> 00:07:06,291
LISTEN, MONA.
I CAN HELP. TALK TO ME.

108
00:07:07,694 --> 00:07:12,897
WELL, I'M A SHOWGIRL
DOWN AT THE CLUB ALI BAR,

109
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:15,934
<i>AND MY BOSS IS IN TROUBLE.</i>

110
00:07:16,002 --> 00:07:18,636
TROUBLE?
WHAT'S YOUR BOSS'S NAME?

111
00:07:18,705 --> 00:07:20,772
- DIRTY WILLY.
- HE DOESN'T BATHE?

112
00:07:20,841 --> 00:07:23,608
NO. PEOPLE JUST CALL HIM THAT.

113
00:07:23,677 --> 00:07:29,080
HE'S A GOOD MAN, TAKES CARE
OF US, AND ALL THE GIRLS
HAVE COMPREHENSIVE DENTAL.

114
00:07:29,148 --> 00:07:34,819
- WOW. THAT'S KEY.
- AND THIS BUCKET OF QUARTERS
IS ALL HE'S GOT LEFT.

115
00:07:34,888 --> 00:07:40,424
AND HE TOLD ME
TO GIVE THIS TO MR. DIXON.

116
00:07:40,494 --> 00:07:42,760
OKAY.

117
00:07:42,829 --> 00:07:46,931
I WILL GET THIS
TO MR. DIXON.

118
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:50,969
WILLY KNOWS THINGS,
MR. ARGYLE--
OH, YEAH?

119
00:07:51,037 --> 00:07:52,937
THINGS THAT HE SHOULDN'T KNOW.

120
00:07:53,006 --> 00:07:57,642
HE NEEDS PROTECTION.
CONSIDER IT DONE,
MS. LISA.

121
00:07:57,711 --> 00:08:01,012
ARGYLE IS ON THE CASE.
[ Giggles ]

122
00:08:02,215 --> 00:08:04,915
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>"ARGYLE IS ON THE CASE"--</i>

123
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:08,219
<i>FIVE WORDS TO SEND A CHILL</i>
<i>DOWN YOUR SPINE.</i>

124
00:08:08,288 --> 00:08:11,756
<i>ARGYLE EMBRACED THE CLICHÉ,</i>
<i>CASTING HIMSELF IN</i>
<i>THE STARRING ROLE...</i>

125
00:08:11,825 --> 00:08:14,993
<i>OF A BIG-TIME PRIVATE EYE</i>
<i>EXTRAORDINAIRE.</i>

126
00:08:15,061 --> 00:08:19,196
<i>DETERMINED TO HELP MONA,</i>
<i>HE MADE HIS WAY BACK</i>
<i>INTO THE CLUB ALI BAR...</i>

127
00:08:19,266 --> 00:08:21,666
<i>AND, LIKE A TRUE DETECTIVE,</i>
<i>WAS LOOKING FOR CLUES--</i>

128
00:08:21,735 --> 00:08:25,703
<i>ANYTHING HE COULD FIND</i>
<i>THAT WOULD LEAD HIM TO WHERE</i>
<i>OR WHAT HAPPENED TO DIRTY WILLY.</i>

129
00:08:25,772 --> 00:08:28,239
<i>BUT HE WASN'T READY</i>
<i>TO BE A STAR.</i>

130
00:08:28,308 --> 00:08:33,210
<i>AS SOON AS THINGS GOT REAL,</i>
<i>ARGYLE WISHED HE'D TAKEN</i>
<i>A BIT PART.</i>

131
00:08:36,549 --> 00:08:38,549
[ Argyle Gasps ]
DIRTY WILLY.

132
00:08:38,618 --> 00:08:42,487
<i>HE'D DONE THE JOB,</i>
<i>SOLVED THE CASE.</i>
<i>HE HAD THE KILLER CORNERED.</i>

133
00:08:42,556 --> 00:08:44,956
-<i> SO ARGYLE DID</i>
<i> WHAT ARGYLE DOES BEST.</i>
- [ Gasps ]

134
00:08:45,025 --> 00:08:48,793
-<i> HE NEVER SAW THE HIT MAN.</i>
<i> WHO COULD AT THAT SPEED?</i>
- WOAH!

135
00:08:48,861 --> 00:08:53,731
<i>HE WAS PRETTY SURE</i>
<i>THE KILLER DIDN'T SEE HIM--</i>
<i>PRETTY SURE.</i>

136
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:56,967
<i>WHICH BRINGS US BACK</i>
<i>TO OUR PISTACHIO-PACKIN' PORKER.</i>

137
00:08:57,036 --> 00:08:58,969
<i>HE WAS WONDERING</i>
<i>THE SAME THING AS ME.</i>

138
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:01,205
- WHERE THE HELL IS MONA?
- WELL, I-I-I DON'T KNOW.

139
00:09:01,274 --> 00:09:04,542
SHE TOLD ME SHE WAS COMIN'
TO SEE YOU, DIXON.
AND NOW SHE'S GONE?

140
00:09:04,611 --> 00:09:07,245
- DID SHE SAY
WHERE SHE WAS GOIN'?
- SHE HASN'T TOLD ME ANYTHING.

141
00:09:07,314 --> 00:09:10,981
- DID SHE LEAVE ANYTHING?
- LOOK. NORMALLY, I DON'T TALK
TO GUN-WIELDING THUGS.

142
00:09:11,050 --> 00:09:16,020
YEAH. YOUR MAMA MUST BE
REAL PROUD OF YOU NOW,
EH, BIG BOY?

143
00:09:18,725 --> 00:09:20,658
NO. SHE'D PROBABLY
GIVE ME A LICKIN'.

144
00:09:21,961 --> 00:09:24,329
MY MAMA'S DEAD.

145
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:31,068
<i>TRUTH IS, I'M NOT A THUG.</i>
<i>MY NAME IS MIKE.</i>
<i>I'M MONA'S BROTHER.</i>

146
00:09:31,137 --> 00:09:34,438
- OH. HI, MIKE.
- HI.

147
00:09:34,508 --> 00:09:38,276
[ Sighs ] IT JUST AIN'T LIKE HER
NOT TO CHECK IN. OUR PARENTS
DIED WHEN WE WERE REAL LITTLE,

148
00:09:38,345 --> 00:09:40,511
<i>AND I MADE A PROMISE TO MOM</i>
<i>THAT I'D TAKE CARE OF MONA.</i>

149
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:44,949
- I JUST GOTTA KNOW
IF SHE'S OKAY.
- [ Sighs ]

150
00:09:45,017 --> 00:09:49,220
YOU WILL. JUST AS SOON
AS WE FIND OUT ANYTHING,
YOU'LL BE THE FIRST TO KNOW.

151
00:09:49,288 --> 00:09:52,957
I PROMISE.
RIGHT, PARTNER?
YEAH.

152
00:09:53,026 --> 00:09:56,594
<i>DICK DIXON IS ON THE CASE,</i>
<i>KICKIN' TAIL AND TAKIN' NAMES.</i>

153
00:09:56,663 --> 00:10:01,332
YOU ARE MR. POSITIVI-TIVITY,
THE SHAH OF "I CAN."
HEY, NOW. SWELL RIDE.

154
00:10:01,401 --> 00:10:04,202
LIKE I ALWAYS SAY,
PRIVATE DICK'S GOTTA
HAVE A RAGTOP.

155
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:06,638
- YOU ARE NOT GOING.
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKIN' ABOUT?

156
00:10:06,707 --> 00:10:10,107
I AM NOT A DETECTIVE. YOU ARE
NOT MY PARTNER. IF I'M GOING
TO HELP, YOU STAY OUTTA MY WAY.

157
00:10:10,176 --> 00:10:13,044
THAT WAS
EXTREMELY HOSTILE.

158
00:10:13,113 --> 00:10:15,946
I CAN'T KEEP SAVING YOUR LIFE
IF YOU KEEP LYING YOURSELF
INTO A CORNER.

159
00:10:16,015 --> 00:10:18,516
YOU HAVE TO THINK.
[ Engine Starts ]
HEY!

160
00:10:18,584 --> 00:10:20,518
[ Engine Stops ]
I'VE BEEN THINKIN'.

161
00:10:20,586 --> 00:10:23,454
I WAS UPSIDE, INSIDE OUT,
LIVIN'<i> LA VIDA LOCA</i>
TILL I MET YOU.

162
00:10:23,523 --> 00:10:28,459
NOW AFTER YOU HELPED ME
AND POP LAST YEAR, I'M MENDIN'
MY WICKED WAYS, YOU KNOW.

163
00:10:28,528 --> 00:10:31,229
<i> I AIN'T HAD NOTHIN'</i>
<i> BUT HONEST JOBS SINCE.</i>

164
00:10:31,298 --> 00:10:36,501
ONLY THING MISSIN'
IS THE LOVE OF MY LIFE.
AND I MET HER LAST WEEK.

165
00:10:43,677 --> 00:10:48,145
- MONA'S THE ONE.
- YOU SPENT SIX MINUTES
WITH HER.

166
00:10:48,214 --> 00:10:53,685
360 GLORIOUS SECONDS,
J-MAN. SOMETHIN' HAPPENED
BETWEEN US, I'M TELLIN' YA.

167
00:10:53,753 --> 00:10:57,122
IT WAS LIKE "ELECTRONICAL"
CHEMICALS OR SOMETHING.

168
00:10:57,190 --> 00:10:59,123
PHEROMONES, BABY,
I'M TELLIN' YA.

169
00:10:59,191 --> 00:11:02,259
AND NOW MY FUTURE
BROTHER-IN-LAW'S WEEPIN'
IN HIS PISTACHIO.

170
00:11:02,329 --> 00:11:05,296
YOU GOTTA LET ME
COME WITH YOU, J-STER.
YOU GOTTA LET ME HELP HER.

171
00:11:05,365 --> 00:11:08,132
J-MAN. J-DOG.
PLEASE, I'M BEGGIN' YA.

172
00:11:08,201 --> 00:11:10,234
PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE,
PLEASE, PLEASE.

173
00:11:10,303 --> 00:11:14,105
<i>THERE ARE CERTAIN TIMES IN LIFE</i>
<i>WHEN YOU NEED TO THINK WITH</i>
<i>YOUR HEART, NOT YOUR HEAD.</i>

174
00:11:14,174 --> 00:11:19,310
<i>THIS WASN'T ONE OF THOSE TIMES,</i>
<i>BUT I THOUGHT IT WAS,</i>
<i>SO I MADE THE FOLLOWING MISTAKE.</i>

175
00:11:19,379 --> 00:11:22,880
PLEASE?
GET IN.

176
00:11:22,949 --> 00:11:25,784
YEAH, YEAH.

177
00:11:25,852 --> 00:11:28,987
<i> [ Engine Starts ]</i>
ARGYLE IS ON THE CASE.
COME ON!

178
00:11:34,794 --> 00:11:37,862
HOW DID I GET IN THIS NIGHTMARE?

179
00:11:37,931 --> 00:11:41,332
WELL, I-I REMEMBER
I WAS WATCHING OUT
FOR JAROD,

180
00:11:41,401 --> 00:11:45,904
AND YOU LOOKED AT ME WITH
BEDROOM EYES, LIKE YOU WANTED
TO DO THE LATE-NIGHT CREEP.

181
00:11:45,972 --> 00:11:49,340
I DID NOT. WE DID NOT.

182
00:11:49,409 --> 00:11:51,976
WELL, HOW CAN YOU BE SURE,
MISS PARKER?

183
00:11:52,045 --> 00:11:54,779
FOR STARTERS,
PIGS AREN'T FLYING,
HELL HASN'T FROZEN OVER,

184
00:11:54,848 --> 00:11:57,648
<i>AND YOU'RE NOT</i>
<i>THE LAST MAN ON EARTH.</i>

185
00:11:57,717 --> 00:12:01,085
[ Rings ]

186
00:12:01,154 --> 00:12:03,687
- WHAT?
- HOW'S THE STAKEOUT GOING?

187
00:12:03,756 --> 00:12:05,990
SYDNEY, HOW ARE YOU?

188
00:12:07,661 --> 00:12:09,594
I... AM FINE.

189
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:12,897
SWEEPER TEAM SAYS
YOU HAVEN'T REPORTED IN.

190
00:12:12,966 --> 00:12:15,066
HUH. SOMETHING CAME UP.

191
00:12:15,135 --> 00:12:19,837
<i>I... OVERSLEPT, BUT--</i>
<i>BUT I WAS JUST GETTING DRESSED.</i>

192
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:22,740
I'LL BE THERE TOMORROW
WITH LYLE AND RAINES.

193
00:12:22,808 --> 00:12:25,577
PARKER, IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

194
00:12:25,645 --> 00:12:28,513
I AM ROLLING NOTHING BUT SEVENS.
[ Chuckles ]

195
00:12:38,592 --> 00:12:42,693
[ Quietly ]
YOU SO MUCH AS HINT AT THIS
WHEN THEY ARRIVE,

196
00:12:42,763 --> 00:12:46,231
<i>I WILL AMPUTATE YOUR HEAD.</i>

197
00:12:46,299 --> 00:12:50,234
- WELL, WHAT ABOUT THIS?
- THERE IS NO "THIS."

198
00:12:50,303 --> 00:12:52,603
NOTHING HAPPENED,
BROOTS.

199
00:12:52,672 --> 00:12:57,408
LIKE I SAID, IT WAS A NIGHTMARE,
AND I'M GLAD I WOKE UP.

200
00:12:57,477 --> 00:13:00,644
WHEN YOU SAY THINGS LIKE THAT,
DO YOU EVEN CONSIDER
MY FEELINGS?

201
00:13:03,416 --> 00:13:05,716
WHAT IS IT ABOUT ME
THAT YOU FIND SO REPULSIVE?

202
00:13:07,787 --> 00:13:10,755
YOU REALLY WANT TO KNOW?
YES. I REALLY
WANT TO KNOW.

203
00:13:10,824 --> 00:13:12,957
OKAY.

204
00:13:13,026 --> 00:13:16,293
NOW YOU SHUT UP
AND LISTEN.

205
00:13:17,497 --> 00:13:22,367
WHAT I FIND SO UTTERLY
UNINSPIRING ABOUT YOU...

206
00:13:22,435 --> 00:13:25,502
IS YOUR IDEA OF RISK
IS TO GO WITHOUT DEODORANT.

207
00:13:25,571 --> 00:13:30,641
WHEN THE BULLETS STOP FLYING,
YOU'RE ALWAYS THE ONE
SHAKING IN THE CORNER.

208
00:13:30,710 --> 00:13:35,813
THAT, IN THE GAME OF LIFE,
IS SECOND STRING.

209
00:13:35,882 --> 00:13:39,584
AND I DON'T WANT
NO SCRUBS.

210
00:13:39,653 --> 00:13:44,755
HEY. STOP, AND LET ME TELL
YOU SOMETHING, AND YOU--

211
00:13:44,824 --> 00:13:47,625
<i>YOU</i> SHUT UP AND LISTEN.

212
00:13:47,694 --> 00:13:50,528
YOU'RE RIGHT.

213
00:13:50,597 --> 00:13:54,164
I HAVE NEVER TAKEN A RISK.

214
00:13:54,233 --> 00:13:57,468
<i>BECAUSE THE WHOLE TIME</i>
<i>I'VE KNOWN YOU, I'VE ONLY</i>
<i>WANTED TO TAKE JUST ONE.</i>

215
00:13:57,537 --> 00:14:00,171
WHICH ONE WOULD THAT BE?

216
00:14:02,776 --> 00:14:04,776
YOU'RE IN YOUR OFFICE.

217
00:14:06,646 --> 00:14:09,647
IT'S LATE, AND I SNEAK IN.

218
00:14:09,716 --> 00:14:14,686
<i>IN ONE HAND I HAVE GARDENIAS,</i>
<i>AND IN THE OTHER I HAVE</i>
<i>A BOTTLE OF SINGLE MALT--</i>

219
00:14:14,754 --> 00:14:17,955
TWO OF YOUR FAVORITE THINGS
IN THE WORLD.

220
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:22,493
<i>AND I FIND THAT LITTLE SPOT</i>
<i>ON THE NAPE OF YOUR NECK,</i>

221
00:14:22,562 --> 00:14:25,463
AND I JUST...
RUB IT THE RIGHT WAY...

222
00:14:25,532 --> 00:14:30,501
<i>TO GET RID OF THAT MIGRAINE</i>
<i>YOU ALWAYS GET ABOUT</i>
<i>6:20 EVERY NIGHT--</i>

223
00:14:30,570 --> 00:14:33,471
THE ONE YOU NEVER TELL
ANYONE ABOUT.

224
00:14:35,274 --> 00:14:39,744
<i> THE TRUTH IS,</i>
<i> IF I HAD JUST ONE SHOT,</i>

225
00:14:39,812 --> 00:14:41,746
YOU KNOW WHAT I'D DO?

226
00:14:43,617 --> 00:14:47,151
I WOULD TAKE YOUR PAIN AWAY.

227
00:14:50,257 --> 00:14:52,990
TRUTH IS, YOU'D BE LUCKY
TO GET A SCRUB LIKE ME.

228
00:14:59,532 --> 00:15:03,100
- DO YOU HEAR THAT, BROOTS?
- WHAT?

229
00:15:10,076 --> 00:15:12,843
PIGS ARE FLYING.

230
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:18,049
<i>[ Man Singing Slow Jazz ]</i>
<i>♪ SO BABY, SAY YOU WILL ♪</i>

231
00:15:18,118 --> 00:15:21,586
<i>♪ NO NEED TO TELL ♪</i>

232
00:15:21,655 --> 00:15:25,557
<i>♪ NO REASON TO DENY IT ♪♪</i>
[ Both Moaning ]

233
00:15:25,625 --> 00:15:28,693
[ Miss Parker Squeals, Giggles ]
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>LIFE IS STRANGE.</i>

234
00:15:28,762 --> 00:15:33,031
<i>ONE HOUR IN THE NEVADA SUN, AND</i>
<i>I HAD MORE UNANSWERED QUESTIONS</i>
<i>THAN THE WARREN COMMISSION.</i>

235
00:15:33,099 --> 00:15:35,467
<i>♪♪ [ Continues ]</i>
<i>THERE WAS DIRTY WILLY'S</i>
<i>MURDER TO SOLVE...</i>

236
00:15:35,535 --> 00:15:38,036
<i>AND MONA,</i>
<i>THE MISSING SHOWGIRL,</i>
<i>TO TRACK DOWN.</i>

237
00:15:38,104 --> 00:15:40,438
<i>BUT ARGYLE HAD TO SEE</i>
<i>HIS FATHER, BENNY.</i>

238
00:15:40,507 --> 00:15:45,843
<i>THE OLD MAN USED TO BE OBSESSED</i>
<i>WITH THE POPE. I WAS ABOUT</i>
<i>TO FIND OUT HE CONVERTED.</i>

239
00:15:45,912 --> 00:15:48,513
WAYNE NEWTON IS MORE
THAN A HOLY MAN.

240
00:15:48,582 --> 00:15:52,417
<i>HE IS THE SHAMAN OF THE STRIP.</i>
<i>HE'S THE DUKE OF DOWNTOWN.</i>

241
00:15:52,485 --> 00:15:55,786
- WAYNE NEWTON
IS LAS VEGAS.
- IF YOU SAY SO.

242
00:15:55,855 --> 00:15:58,022
YOU KNOW, I MET HIM ONCE,
SORT OF?

243
00:15:58,091 --> 00:16:01,726
MY ADELLA AND I, UH,
SAW HIM IN VEGAS LONG AGO.

244
00:16:01,794 --> 00:16:06,097
<i> WHO'D HAVE THOUGHT</i>
<i> I'D BE BACK HERE IN VEGAS</i>
<i> WITH ARGYLE...</i>

245
00:16:06,165 --> 00:16:08,766
LIVIN' IN THIS
EXQUISITE GOLF VILLA?

246
00:16:08,835 --> 00:16:12,169
<i>[ Man, In Distance ]</i>
<i>FORE!</i>

247
00:16:12,238 --> 00:16:14,339
DRIVING RANGE IS OPEN.
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>SORRY.</i>

248
00:16:14,407 --> 00:16:19,177
<i> YEAH. THE ONLY ONE MISSIN'</i>
<i> IS MY ADELLA.</i>

249
00:16:19,245 --> 00:16:22,146
THIS WEEK WOULD'VE BEEN
OUR 50th ANNIVERSARY.

250
00:16:22,215 --> 00:16:26,785
SHE WAS MY INSPIRATION, JAROD.
SHE'S THE REASON I'M WRITIN'
A SONG FOR WAYNE.

251
00:16:26,853 --> 00:16:29,487
- HEY, POP, WE--
WE DON'T HAVE TIME FOR THAT.
-<i> OH, SURE WE DO.</i>

252
00:16:29,556 --> 00:16:31,622
<i> THE BIG "W,"</i>
<i> HE CHANGED OUR LIVES,</i>

253
00:16:31,692 --> 00:16:35,260
SO MY ADELLA SUGGESTED THAT
I SHOULD WRITE HIM A SONG,

254
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:38,329
SORT OF A COMPANION PIECE
TO "DANKE SCHOEN."

255
00:16:38,398 --> 00:16:41,699
SHE SAID,
"CALL IT 'AUF WIEDERSEHEN,'"

256
00:16:41,768 --> 00:16:44,936
AND HERE GOES NOTHING.

257
00:16:45,005 --> 00:16:48,439
♪♪ [ Introduction ]

258
00:16:48,508 --> 00:16:50,441
♪♪ [ Ends ]

259
00:16:53,212 --> 00:16:56,614
- WHERE'S THE SONG?
- IT'S STILL A WORK IN PROGRESS.
IT'LL BE READY BY TOMORROW.

260
00:16:56,683 --> 00:17:00,552
- WHAT'S HAPPENING TOMORROW?
- UH, WAYNE IS PLAYIN'
IN A CHARITY TOURNAMENT,

261
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:03,354
AND HE WILL BE
RIGHT THERE PUTTING,

262
00:17:03,423 --> 00:17:06,257
AND I WILL BE
RIGHT HERE STANDING--

263
00:17:06,326 --> 00:17:09,294
♪ WHEN I HIT HIM
WITH THE RAZZAMATAZZ ♪

264
00:17:09,362 --> 00:17:13,865
YOU KNOW, I'VE NEVER
ACTUALLY PLAYED GOLF, BUT, UM,
WON'T THAT DISTURB HIS GAME?

265
00:17:14,935 --> 00:17:17,302
OH, YEAH.

266
00:17:17,370 --> 00:17:21,472
WELL, YEAH, BUT IT'S WORTH IT
FOR MY ADELLA'S LAST WISH,
ISN'T IT?

267
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:23,741
IT'S MORE THAN WORTH IT.

268
00:17:23,810 --> 00:17:26,544
YEAH. GOOD.
AND THE BIG "W"
WILL LOVE IT, POP,

269
00:17:26,613 --> 00:17:29,313
<i>BUT WE GOTTA GET OUT OF HERE.</i>
<i>WE GOTTA CATCH OURSELVES</i>
<i>A KILLER.</i>

270
00:17:29,383 --> 00:17:32,383
I GOT ME A SONG
TO WRITE.
CATCH YOU LATER, POP.

271
00:17:32,452 --> 00:17:35,920
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>IT WAS NICE TO SEE BENNY AGAIN,</i>
<i>BUT ARGYLE WAS RIGHT.</i>

272
00:17:35,988 --> 00:17:41,326
<i>WE DID HAVE A KILLER</i>
<i>TO CATCH. SO WE WENT BACK</i>
<i>TO THE SCENE OF THE CRIME.</i>

273
00:17:41,394 --> 00:17:44,329
OKAY.
UH, DIRTY WILLY BOUGHT IT
RIGHT ABOUT HERE,

274
00:17:44,397 --> 00:17:46,731
AND I SAW THE KILLER
STANDING RIGHT OVER THERE.

275
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,700
<i> HEY, FUNNY FACE,</i>
<i> THIS AREA'S OFF LIMITS,</i>
<i> ALL RIGHT?</i>

276
00:17:49,769 --> 00:17:51,869
I GOT TOP-NOTCH TALENT
MAKIN' THEIR WAY THROUGH HERE...

277
00:17:51,938 --> 00:17:54,172
TO THE MOST GLORIOUS STAGE
IN LAS VEGAS,

278
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:57,675
AND I CAN'T HAVE YOU
OR THAT THING YOU CALL A SUIT
IN THE WAY.

279
00:17:57,744 --> 00:18:00,678
-LET ME EXPLAIN.
-NO. THERE'S NO EXPLAININ'
THAT, AND WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

280
00:18:00,747 --> 00:18:03,114
- MY NAME IS DICK DIXON.
- YOU'RE DICK DIXON?

281
00:18:03,183 --> 00:18:05,784
- OH!
- YOU SLEPT WITH MY WIFE,
YOU SCUMBALL!

282
00:18:05,852 --> 00:18:10,121
- I DON'T EVEN KNOW YOUR WIFE.
- THRIFTY SUITES, NUMBER 38.
RING A BELL, PUMPKIN?

283
00:18:10,190 --> 00:18:13,691
<i>HEY, HEY, HEY, HALF-PINT,</i>
<i>THIS AIN'T ABOUT YOUR OLD LADY</i>
<i>GIVIN' ROOM SERVICE, ALL RIGHT?</i>

284
00:18:13,759 --> 00:18:16,427
WE'RE TRYIN' TO FIND
MONA JEFFRIES.
YEAH, WELL, I AIN'T SEEN HER.

285
00:18:16,496 --> 00:18:19,396
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
ABOUT IT, TOUGH GUY?
[ Yelps ]

286
00:18:19,465 --> 00:18:21,632
YOU SEE THAT?
THERE GOES MY CHIVAS.

287
00:18:21,701 --> 00:18:23,801
WHERE'D YOU LEARN
HOW TO DO THAT?
I RAN A DOJO ONCE.

288
00:18:23,869 --> 00:18:26,904
NOW TELL US WHAT YOU KNOW.
OKAY. I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT I TOLD THE COPS, ALL RIGHT?

289
00:18:26,973 --> 00:18:28,906
MONA AIN'T YOUR TYPICAL
SHOWGIRL, ALL RIGHT? SHE--

290
00:18:28,975 --> 00:18:32,110
SHE WON'T SHOW HER CONES,
AND SHE SAVES HER DOUGH.
[ Yelps ]

291
00:18:32,178 --> 00:18:35,146
- SHE BOUGHT A CONDO
OUTSIDE OF TOWN.
- WHERE?

292
00:18:35,214 --> 00:18:38,549
[ Yelps ]
OKAY! GOD!
I'LL TELL YA! GEEZ!

293
00:18:42,255 --> 00:18:45,423
I GOT YOUR BACK, J-MAN.
OH, THAT'S VERY COMFORTING.

294
00:18:45,491 --> 00:18:50,228
EITHER MY MONA'S REAL MESSY,
J-MAN, OR SOMETHIN' REAL BAD
HAPPENED TO HER.

295
00:18:50,297 --> 00:18:53,831
<i> YOU CAN STOP RIGHT THERE.</i>
<i> LET'S SEE SOME I.D.</i>

296
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:57,902
- THE I.D.'S OUT IN THE CAR.
MY NAME IS DICK DIXON.
- YOU'RE DICK DIXON?

297
00:18:57,971 --> 00:19:00,905
- YES.
- YOU SLEPT WITH ONE
OF OUR DEPUTIES.

298
00:19:00,974 --> 00:19:03,107
<i> SHE LEFT THE FORCE</i>
<i> 'CAUSE OF YOU.</i>

299
00:19:07,313 --> 00:19:10,181
I SEEM TO HAVE
THAT EFFECT ON PEOPLE.

300
00:19:10,249 --> 00:19:13,584
- WHAT HAPPENED HERE?
- BEEN A WHILE SINCE YOU CRACKED
YOUR DETECTIVE HANDBOOK, HUH?

301
00:19:13,653 --> 00:19:17,621
<i>WE GOT A REPORT OF</i>
<i>A DISTURBANCE. DOOR WAS JIMMIED,</i>
<i>PLACE HAD BEEN TRASHED,</i>

302
00:19:17,691 --> 00:19:20,558
<i>BUT HER CAR KEYS, PURSE</i>
<i>AND VALUABLES ARE STILL HERE.</i>

303
00:19:21,728 --> 00:19:25,096
- MONA WAS LEAVING?
- NO. SHE WAS KIDNAPPED.

304
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:43,380
<i> [ Knocking ]</i>

305
00:19:45,685 --> 00:19:49,153
- YOU GONNA GET THAT?
-<i> [ Knocking Continues ]</i>

306
00:19:49,222 --> 00:19:51,789
THOSE ARE
THE LATE-NIGHT CREEPERS.

307
00:19:52,925 --> 00:19:56,026
IT IS THE HONEYMOON SUITE.
<i> [ Knocking ]</i>

308
00:19:56,095 --> 00:19:58,896
<i> [ Door Closes ]</i>

309
00:19:58,965 --> 00:20:02,900
<i>[ Faucet Turns, Water Running ]</i>
[ Martial Arts Grunts ]

310
00:20:02,969 --> 00:20:05,603
[ Imitating Elvis ]
OH, YEAH.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

311
00:20:05,672 --> 00:20:10,074
OH, SYD. YOU'RE HERE EARLY.
[ Clears Throat ]
I THOUGHT SOMETHING WAS WRONG.

312
00:20:10,143 --> 00:20:12,242
<i>[ Water Running Continues ]</i>
OH, NO. NO.

313
00:20:12,311 --> 00:20:15,112
NO. AS A MATTER OF FACT,
THINGS ARE GONNA BE DIFFERENT
FROM NOW ON.

314
00:20:15,181 --> 00:20:17,881
<i>[ Water Stops ]</i>
<i>BROOTS, YOU ARE GONNA PAY FOR...</i>

315
00:20:17,951 --> 00:20:19,883
<i>USING ALL THE HOT WATER,</i>
<i>YOU MORON!</i>

316
00:20:19,953 --> 00:20:21,885
YOU WERE SAYING, BROOTS?

317
00:20:21,954 --> 00:20:25,890
SYD, PLEASE TELL ME
YOU'RE HERE TO RELIEVE ME.

318
00:20:25,958 --> 00:20:29,293
BEING COOPED UP
WITH FELIX UNGAR HERE MAKES ME
GLAD TO SEE YOUR SORRY MUG.

319
00:20:29,362 --> 00:20:33,130
<i> LYLE AND I</i>
<i> ARE REGISTERED</i>
<i> AT CAESARS.</i>

320
00:20:33,199 --> 00:20:35,132
SEPARATE ROOMS?

321
00:20:35,201 --> 00:20:38,402
WELL, SEPARATE SUITES.
[ Scoffs ]

322
00:20:38,470 --> 00:20:41,605
<i> [ Sydney ]</i>
<i> LYLE WILL BE HERE LATER.</i>
<i> PERHAPS WE CAN TAKE OVER.</i>

323
00:20:41,675 --> 00:20:46,177
HOPEFULLY, I WON'T HAVE
PLUGGED BROOTS BEFORE THEN.
CALL ME WHEN HE GETS HERE.

324
00:20:50,683 --> 00:20:54,752
- WHAT?
- I THOUGHT THINGS WERE GONNA
BE DIFFERENT BETWEEN US.

325
00:20:54,821 --> 00:20:57,121
THERE IS NO "US."

326
00:20:57,190 --> 00:21:01,492
AT LEAST...
NOT THAT THEY KNOW OF.

327
00:21:03,863 --> 00:21:07,831
<i> COULD YOU IMAGINE</i>
<i> WHAT THEY WOULD DO</i>
<i> IF THEY KNEW?</i>

328
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:11,869
RIGHT. RIGHT. WE DON'T--
WE DON'T WANNA GIVE THEM
ANY AMMUNITION, NOW DO WE?

329
00:21:11,938 --> 00:21:14,806
SPEAKING OF WHICH,

330
00:21:14,874 --> 00:21:18,475
MY CLIP IS EMPTY.

331
00:21:18,544 --> 00:21:21,512
OH, YEAH.
I GET IT, BABY.

332
00:21:21,581 --> 00:21:25,349
BUT IF WE'RE GONNA DO THIS--
[ Whispering ]
WE GOTTA DO IT RIGHT.

333
00:21:25,418 --> 00:21:28,619
I'VE ALWAYS HAD A LITTLE FANTASY
I WANT TO LIVE OUT WITH YOU.

334
00:21:28,688 --> 00:21:31,789
BUT FIRST I WANT YOU
TO CALL ME...

335
00:21:32,858 --> 00:21:35,058
"PUFF DADDY."

336
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:37,995
SAY IT.
<i> SAY</i> IT.

337
00:21:39,065 --> 00:21:42,132
PUFF--
[ Inhales ]
DADDY.

338
00:21:42,201 --> 00:21:44,202
OH!

339
00:21:44,270 --> 00:21:46,637
[ Sighs ]

340
00:21:46,706 --> 00:21:50,675
- ♪♪ [ Soul, Slow ]
WELCOME TO STATION WEFUNK--
- [ Lip-synching ]

341
00:21:50,743 --> 00:21:53,477
[ Continues Lip-synching ]
BETTER KNOWN AS "WE-FUNK,"
OR DEEPER STILL,

342
00:21:53,546 --> 00:21:57,682
"THE MOTHER SHIP CONNECTION,"
HOME OF THE EXTRATERRESTRIAL
BROTHERS,

343
00:21:57,750 --> 00:22:01,119
<i>DEALERS OF FUNKY MUSIC,</i>
<i>"P" FUNK,</i>

344
00:22:01,187 --> 00:22:03,754
UNCUT FUNK, THE BOMB.

345
00:22:03,822 --> 00:22:06,857
♪ MAKE MY FUNK
THE "P" FUNK ♪

346
00:22:06,926 --> 00:22:09,527
♪ I WANT THE FUNK UNCUT ♪

347
00:22:09,596 --> 00:22:12,063
<i> ♪ OH, MAKE MY FUNK</i>
<i> THE "P" FUNK ♪</i>

348
00:22:12,132 --> 00:22:14,064
<i>♪ I WANTS TO GET FUNKED UP ♪</i>

349
00:22:14,134 --> 00:22:17,801
<i>♪ HIM, I WANT THE BOMB</i>
<i>  I WANT THE "P" FUNK, Y'ALL ♪</i>

350
00:22:17,870 --> 00:22:19,870
<i> ♪ DON'T WANT MY FUNK</i>
<i> STEPPED ON ♪</i>

351
00:22:19,939 --> 00:22:22,606
<i>♪ MAKE MY FUNK THE "P" FUNK ♪</i>

352
00:22:22,675 --> 00:22:25,609
<i>HOME OF</i>
<i>THE EXTRATERRESTRIAL BROTHERS.</i>
<i>♪ BEFORE I TAKE IT HOME ♪♪</i>

353
00:22:26,612 --> 00:22:29,780
<i>♪♪ [ Saxophone ]</i>

354
00:22:29,849 --> 00:22:31,782
<i>GETTIN' DEEP.</i>

355
00:22:31,851 --> 00:22:33,851
<i>♪♪ [ Saxophone Continues ]</i>

356
00:22:36,755 --> 00:22:40,057
<i>ONCE UPON A TIME</i>
<i>CALLED "RIGHT NOW."</i>

357
00:22:40,125 --> 00:22:43,393
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>THEY SAY THAT LIFE</i>
<i>IS STRANGER THAN FICTION.</i>

358
00:22:43,463 --> 00:22:47,098
<i>MINE CERTAINLY HAS BEEN,</i>
<i>AND THIS WAS NO EXCEPTION.</i>

359
00:22:47,167 --> 00:22:50,067
<i>MONA WAS KIDNAPPED,</i>
<i>BUT BY WHOM?</i>

360
00:22:50,136 --> 00:22:53,737
<i>WHATEVER TROUBLE HER BOSS,</i>
<i>DIRTY WILLY, FOUND,</i>
<i>IT HAD CERTAINLY FOUND HER,</i>

361
00:22:53,806 --> 00:22:57,308
<i>AND IT WAS ONLY A MATTER OF TIME</i>
<i>BEFORE IT FOUND US.</i>

362
00:22:57,376 --> 00:23:01,512
<i>I DID WHAT SYNDEY</i>
<i>ALWAYS TAUGHT ME: WHEN IN DOUBT,</i>
<i>GO BACK TO THE EVIDENCE.</i>

363
00:23:01,580 --> 00:23:04,982
A COUPLE OF THINGS
JUST DON'T MAKE ANY SENSE.
ACCORDING TO THE AUTOPSY REPORT,

364
00:23:05,051 --> 00:23:08,152
WHAT KILLED DIRTY WILLY
WAS LOW LEVELS OF OXYGEN
IN HIS TISSUES...

365
00:23:08,221 --> 00:23:10,755
DUE TO HYPOTHERMIA--
EXTREME COLD.

366
00:23:10,823 --> 00:23:13,257
HE FROZE TO DEATH.
IN VEGAS?

367
00:23:13,326 --> 00:23:17,127
AND HE HAD SEVERAL
ICE PICK HOLES IN HIS HANDS.

368
00:23:17,196 --> 00:23:19,197
I'M THINKIN' TORTURE.

369
00:23:21,568 --> 00:23:23,500
WAIT A SECOND, J-MAN.

370
00:23:23,570 --> 00:23:26,403
YOU DON'T THINK
WHO'S EVER DOIN' THIS
MIGHT, YOU KNOW,

371
00:23:26,472 --> 00:23:28,272
POKE MONA LIKE THAT?
LET'S HOPE NOT.

372
00:23:30,176 --> 00:23:33,744
ACCORDING TO THIS FILE,
HE IS THE NUMBER ONE SUSPECT:

373
00:23:33,813 --> 00:23:38,348
<i>CONSTANTIN FALZONE--</i>
<i>AN EXTORTIONIST</i>
<i>FOR THE POSAVAC CRIME FAMILY.</i>

374
00:23:38,417 --> 00:23:41,252
WHAT OTHER PART
OF YOUR TWO-PLUS-TWO CASE
DON'T ADD UP TO FOUR?

375
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:44,188
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>DIRTY WILLY WEIGHED</i>
<i>OVER 300 POUNDS.</i>

376
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:47,958
<i>FROZEN OR NOT,</i>
<i>THAT'S A LOT OF WILLY</i>
<i>FOR ONE MAN TO CARRY AROUND.</i>

377
00:23:48,027 --> 00:23:50,427
- WAIT.
WHAT ARE YOU SAYIN', "J"?
- THERE WERE TWO KILLERS...

378
00:23:50,497 --> 00:23:52,997
WHO TORTURED DIRTY WILLY
AND FROZE HIM TO DEATH.

379
00:23:53,065 --> 00:23:55,933
<i>QUESTION IS,</i>
<i>WHAT DID THEY WANT OUT OF HIM?</i>

380
00:23:56,002 --> 00:24:01,606
[ Exhales ]
THAT'S EASY, BABY--
CASH, DO-RE-MI, J-MAN.

381
00:24:01,674 --> 00:24:04,441
EVERYBODY KNOWS FALZONE
COLLECTS AROUND TOWN,

382
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:06,878
<i> SO MAYBE DIRTY WILLY</i>
<i> COULDN'T COME UP</i>
<i> WITH THE GREEN,</i>

383
00:24:06,946 --> 00:24:09,146
AND THE TWINS
GET P.O.'d WITH HIM.

384
00:24:09,215 --> 00:24:12,349
- TWINS?
- FALZONE'S GOT THESE
FRIGIDAIRES THAT WORK FOR HIM.

385
00:24:12,418 --> 00:24:15,920
CALLS 'EM
HIS CADDIES.
CADDIES? WHY?

386
00:24:15,988 --> 00:24:18,389
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>FALZONE-- SIN CITY OLD-TIMER.</i>

387
00:24:18,457 --> 00:24:22,492
<i>DOESN'T CARE ABOUT</i>
<i>SHOPPING MALLS, PIRATE SHIPS OR</i>
<i>THE EIFFEL TOWER IN THE DESERT.</i>

388
00:24:22,562 --> 00:24:25,897
<i>HE'S ONLY INTERESTED IN CASH...</i>
<i>AND A THREE HANDICAP.</i>

389
00:24:25,965 --> 00:24:29,366
J-ROD, THOSE TWO GOONS
KILLED DIRTY WILLY
AND KIDNAPPED MY MONA.

390
00:24:29,435 --> 00:24:31,635
<i>I SAY WE WASTE 'EM</i>
<i>AND SNAG FALZONE.</i>

391
00:24:31,704 --> 00:24:35,138
NO. WE MEET FALZONE
OUT THERE ON HIS OWN TURF.

392
00:24:35,207 --> 00:24:37,140
BUT YOU DON'T KNOW
HOW TO PLAY.

393
00:24:37,210 --> 00:24:40,411
IT'S ALL GEOMETRY
AND PHYSICS.
HOW HARD COULD THAT BE?

394
00:24:40,479 --> 00:24:44,514
<i>[ Narrating ] SYDNEY ALWAYS</i>
<i>TAUGHT ME, THE MOST DIFFICULT</i>
<i>PRETENDS HAVE AN INNER SECRET.</i>

395
00:24:44,584 --> 00:24:48,318
<i>ONCE YOU REVEAL THAT SECRET,</i>
<i>IT COMES NATURALLY.</i>

396
00:25:31,164 --> 00:25:33,096
<i> [ Club Hits Bushes ]</i>
<i> [ Bird Squawking ]</i>

397
00:25:35,601 --> 00:25:37,101
<i>[ Dog Barks ]</i>

398
00:25:41,140 --> 00:25:44,241
<i>IN 56 MINUTES,</i>
<i>I FOUND THE SECRET</i>
<i>TO A PERFECT GOLF GAME.</i>

399
00:25:44,310 --> 00:25:46,476
<i>I'LL SHARE IT WITH YOU SOMETIME.</i>

400
00:25:46,545 --> 00:25:49,112
<i>THE TWINS WERE IMPRESSED,</i>
<i>JUST LIKE I SAID.</i>

401
00:25:49,181 --> 00:25:51,115
<i>FALZONE WANTED TO TAKE ME ON.</i>

402
00:25:53,118 --> 00:25:55,785
<i>THEN I TOLD THEM</i>
<i>I WAS DICK DIXON.</i>
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

403
00:25:55,854 --> 00:25:58,422
<i>GUESS WHICH ONE'S MARRIED.</i>

404
00:25:58,491 --> 00:26:03,193
<i>THE TWINS PROMISED</i>
<i>TO GET US TO FALZONE,</i>
<i>WHICH THEY DID.</i>

405
00:26:03,262 --> 00:26:07,765
<i>HOWEVER, IN TRUE CHANDLERESQUE</i>
<i>FASHION, WE FOUND OUT</i>
<i>IT WAS WITH A TWIST.</i>

406
00:26:07,834 --> 00:26:10,300
<i>SOMEONE ELSE</i>
<i>HAD GOTTEN TO HIM FIRST.</i>

407
00:26:12,371 --> 00:26:15,740
<i>AND TO THINK</i>
<i>I WASTED 56 MINUTES.</i>

408
00:26:18,678 --> 00:26:23,380
<i>RAYMOND CHANDLER ALWAYS SAID,</i>
<i>"THE BEST WAY TO GET A READER'S</i>
<i> ATTENTION IS WITH A DEAD BODY."</i>

409
00:26:23,449 --> 00:26:25,916
<i>BUT OF COURSE, CHANDLER</i>
<i>WASN'T WRITING THIS ONE.</i>

410
00:26:26,986 --> 00:26:30,154
[ Gasping ]
I GOT BALLS!

411
00:26:31,823 --> 00:26:35,559
<i> [ Splashing ]</i>
<i> I GOT BALLS.</i>

412
00:26:37,229 --> 00:26:41,865
UNBE-FRIGGIN-LIEVABLE.
PEOPLE ACTUALLY
THROW THESE AWAY.

413
00:26:41,934 --> 00:26:45,770
AND THAT MAKES THEM YOURS.
<i> POSSESSION IS 9/10ths.</i>

414
00:26:45,838 --> 00:26:50,341
YOU OUGHTA KNOW.
I HEAR DICK DIXON STEALS WIVES.

415
00:26:50,409 --> 00:26:54,679
AND I HEAR YOU HANG
DIRTY WILLYS. AND NOW
YOU'VE KIDNAPPED MONA JEFFRIES.

416
00:26:54,747 --> 00:26:57,581
HOW COME I GET THE FEELING
YOU CHEAT AT GOLF?

417
00:26:57,649 --> 00:27:00,684
IF YOU'RE NOT CHEATING,
YOU'RE NOT PLAYING.

418
00:27:00,752 --> 00:27:04,121
-<i> HEY, WE WANT MONA BACK.</i>
- WHO ARE YOU-- LITTLE DICK?

419
00:27:04,190 --> 00:27:06,390
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL SHOW YOU LITTLE,
YA BIG FREAK.

420
00:27:06,459 --> 00:27:11,762
HEY. DIRTY WILLY NEVER
CAME UP SHORT, SO THERE'S
NO REASON TO KILL HIM.

421
00:27:11,831 --> 00:27:15,599
<i> AS FOR MONA,</i>
<i> A VIAGRA-POPPIN' MAN</i>
<i> SUCH AS MYSELF...</i>

422
00:27:15,668 --> 00:27:18,969
<i> CAN ONLY PRAY TO ENJOY</i>
<i> A MUFFIN LIKE THAT</i>
<i> IN THE MORNING.</i>

423
00:27:19,038 --> 00:27:24,674
ALL RIGHT. THAT'S IT. YOU AND ME
GONNA THROW RIGHT NOW, PAISAN.
I HAD IT WITH THIS MOOK.

424
00:27:24,743 --> 00:27:28,812
<i>HEY. I GOT NO BEEF</i>
<i>WITH DIRTY WILLY.</i>
<i>I GOT NO BEEF WITH YOU, DIXON.</i>

425
00:27:28,881 --> 00:27:32,616
<i> MONA ASKED ME FOR HELP.</i>
<i> SHE SAID THAT DIRTY WILLY</i>
<i> WAS GETTIN' SQUEEZED...</i>

426
00:27:32,685 --> 00:27:36,220
BY, UM, A COUPLE
OF GOONS BY THE NAME
OF THE FROST BROTHERS.

427
00:27:36,289 --> 00:27:40,090
[ Together ]
THE FROST BROTHERS?
<i> THE FROST BROTHERS.</i>

428
00:27:40,159 --> 00:27:44,395
NOW I GOT MY FINGER IN EVERY
CASINO IN THIS WHOLE TOWN.
I NEVER HEARD OF THESE GUYS.

429
00:27:44,464 --> 00:27:47,464
OKAY? SO THAT'S IT.
THAT'S ALL I KNOW. ALL RIGHT?
ARE WE DONE? ARE WE DONE?

430
00:27:48,534 --> 00:27:51,135
LET'S GO.
LET'S GO.

431
00:27:52,872 --> 00:27:55,673
GIVE ME MY BALLS.

432
00:28:01,246 --> 00:28:05,582
♪♪ [ Humming ]
ROOM SERVICE.

433
00:28:05,651 --> 00:28:08,718
I WAS JUST TALKIN'
TO THE MANAGER. YOU WON'T
BELIEVE WHAT HE WAS TELLING ME.

434
00:28:08,787 --> 00:28:12,189
-<i> AND WHAT WOULD THAT BE,</i>
<i> MR. BROOTS?</i>
- GLAD YOU COULD JOIN US.

435
00:28:12,258 --> 00:28:16,694
<i>[ Raines ]</i>
<i>CENTRE EMPLOYEES OF OPPOSITE</i>
<i>GENDERS DON'T ROOM TOGETHER.</i>

436
00:28:16,762 --> 00:28:20,130
<i> JUST SHOW HIM.</i>

437
00:28:20,199 --> 00:28:23,467
TAKEN BY A SECURITY CAMERA AT
McCARRAN INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT.

438
00:28:23,536 --> 00:28:26,670
<i> IT'S OF JAROD</i>
<i> HEADING FOR THE RUNWAY.</i>
<i> HE SKIPPED TOWN.</i>

439
00:28:26,739 --> 00:28:29,973
YOUR THEORY ISN'T HOLDING.
IT'S TIME TO GO HOME.

440
00:28:30,042 --> 00:28:34,044
NO, BUT THE-- THE E-MAIL
SAID THAT HE WAS GONNA BE HERE.
W-WE HAVE TO STAY.

441
00:28:34,112 --> 00:28:37,180
- BROOTS, IT'S OVER.
- NO. I JUST TALKED
TO THE MANAGER.

442
00:28:37,249 --> 00:28:39,850
HE TOOK A RESERVATION
LAST NIGHT UNDER THE NAME
OF "JAROD SIEGEL"--

443
00:28:39,919 --> 00:28:42,653
<i>AS IN "BUGSY SIEGEL,"</i>
<i>THE MAN WHO CREATED VEGAS.</i>

444
00:28:42,722 --> 00:28:44,855
A RESERVATION DOESN'T MEAN
HE'S GONNA SHOW.

445
00:28:44,924 --> 00:28:46,857
- WE'RE LEAVING.
- WE'RE STAYING.

446
00:28:47,860 --> 00:28:50,527
DID HE JUST IGNORE US?

447
00:28:50,596 --> 00:28:53,697
YOU WANNA BARGE IN HERE
AND TRY AND SCARE ME?
YOU GO AHEAD.

448
00:28:53,766 --> 00:28:59,703
<i>BUT DON'T QUESTION MY SKILLS.</i>
<i>I'M NOT SECOND STRING ANYMORE.</i>
<i>I DO A JOB, AND I DO IT WELL.</i>

449
00:28:59,771 --> 00:29:03,840
AND IF YOUR PARANOID MINDS
CAN'T TAKE THAT, THEN YOU
CAN GO CHASE THAT PHOTO.

450
00:29:03,909 --> 00:29:06,143
<i> MISS PARKER AND I</i>
<i> WILL CATCH JAROD.</i>

451
00:29:14,253 --> 00:29:16,454
ENJOY YOUR BREAKFAST.

452
00:29:17,890 --> 00:29:20,891
[ Wheels Squeaking ]

453
00:29:29,601 --> 00:29:32,436
YOU BETTER HOPE
WE CATCH JAROD,
OR WE'RE THROUGH.

454
00:29:32,504 --> 00:29:34,504
YOU MEAN US?
I MEAN OUR NECKS.

455
00:29:39,045 --> 00:29:41,278
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>AS ARGYLE AND I</i>
<i>DROVE BACK TO BENNY'S,</i>

456
00:29:41,347 --> 00:29:45,048
<i>WE KNEW THAT WITHOUT</i>
<i>THE MYSTERIOUS FROST BROTHERS,</i>
<i>THERE WAS NO MONA...</i>

457
00:29:45,117 --> 00:29:48,218
<i>AND NO DREAM FOR ARGYLE.</i>

458
00:29:48,287 --> 00:29:51,588
<i>BUT ARGYLE'S DREAM</i>
<i>WASN'T THE ONLY ONE IN JEOPARDY.</i>

459
00:29:51,657 --> 00:29:55,192
-<i> OH, THOSE BASTARDS.</i>
<i> BASTARDS, ALL OF THEM!</i>
- BENNY, WHAT HAPPENED?

460
00:29:55,261 --> 00:29:58,328
THERE I AM.
I AM STANDING THERE
IN THE BUNKER.

461
00:29:58,397 --> 00:30:01,731
I AM HALFWAY
INTO MY "OVERATURE,"
AND THEY GRAB ME.

462
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:04,701
WAYNE'S BODYGUARDS.
OH, BITE YOUR TONGUE.
WAYNE'S PEOPLE...

463
00:30:04,770 --> 00:30:07,271
WOULD NEVER DO THAT
WITH A RAKE.

464
00:30:07,339 --> 00:30:10,974
AH, IT WAS THOSE LOWLIFES
THAT WORK FOR THE OTHER HALF
OF WAYNE'S THREESOME--

465
00:30:11,043 --> 00:30:13,610
THOSE "MUGICIANS"
WITH THE BIG HAIR?

466
00:30:13,679 --> 00:30:16,312
IT'S A GOOD THING
THEY DIDN'T BRING
THEIR TIGERS, BOY.

467
00:30:19,918 --> 00:30:24,187
NO. AND I KNOW
HE WOULD'VE LOVED IT.
HE WOULD'VE LOVED IT.

468
00:30:24,256 --> 00:30:26,423
OF COURSE HE WOULD HAVE.

469
00:30:26,491 --> 00:30:29,659
- WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH HIM?
- WE HAVEN'T FOUND MONA YET.

470
00:30:29,728 --> 00:30:35,398
OH, BOY. OH, BOY.
IT'S ALWAYS A GIRL,
ISN'T IT?

471
00:30:36,868 --> 00:30:39,302
LET ME LET YOU IN
ON A LITTLE TINY SECRET.

472
00:30:39,371 --> 00:30:41,304
HE'S JUST EXACTLY LIKE ME.

473
00:30:41,373 --> 00:30:46,409
- NO.
- OH, YES. I WAS WILD.
I WAS UNCHECKED,

474
00:30:46,478 --> 00:30:48,745
UNTIL MY ADELLA TAMED ME.

475
00:30:48,814 --> 00:30:53,450
<i> I STILL REMEMBER THAT TRIP</i>
<i> TO VEGAS. WE WANTED</i>
<i> TO GET AWAY FROM IT ALL.</i>

476
00:30:53,518 --> 00:30:58,288
DR. KANAPA HAD TOLD US
THAT WE WOULDN'T BE ABLE
TO HAVE A FAMILY,

477
00:30:58,357 --> 00:31:01,758
<i> AND I KNOW</i>
<i> IT WAS REALLY TOUGH</i>
<i> FOR HER.</i>

478
00:31:01,827 --> 00:31:03,760
BUT MY ADELLA--

479
00:31:03,829 --> 00:31:07,931
GOD, SHE LOOKED SO BEAUTIFUL
THE NIGHT WE WENT TO SEE WAYNE.

480
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:13,069
<i>YA NEVER SAW A POLKA DOT DRESS</i>
<i>LIKE THAT IN YOUR LIFE.</i>

481
00:31:13,138 --> 00:31:15,772
WELL, BIG WAYNE--

482
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:19,943
HE PICKS HER OUT
OF THE WHOLE CROWD,

483
00:31:20,012 --> 00:31:24,714
<i> AND HE SANG "DANKE SCHOEN"</i>
<i> RIGHT TO HER.</i>

484
00:31:24,783 --> 00:31:27,283
- IT WAS--
- LIKE A DREAM.

485
00:31:27,352 --> 00:31:33,290
YEAH. THAT NIGHT,
ADELLA CAME BACK
TO THE MOTOR COURT...

486
00:31:33,359 --> 00:31:35,659
ALL GIDDY
FROM WAYNE'S SHOW,
YOU KNOW?

487
00:31:35,728 --> 00:31:41,364
<i>AND WE DROVE THE CATTLE ACROSS</i>
<i>THE PRAIRIE ALL NIGHT LONG,</i>
<i>IF YOU CATCH MY MEANING,</i>

488
00:31:43,101 --> 00:31:45,836
AND... WE WERE BLESSED.

489
00:31:45,905 --> 00:31:50,674
- YOU CONCEIVED ARGYLE.
- ROLLED A HARD EIGHT.
[ Chuckles ]

490
00:31:50,742 --> 00:31:53,944
-<i> [ Benny ] SO NOW, WHEN I SEE</i>
<i>  HIM GOIN' THROUGH ALL THIS--</i>
- [ Dog Whimpers ]

491
00:31:54,013 --> 00:31:58,882
<i>I THINK, "WHERE WOULD I BE TODAY</i>
<i>IF IT WEREN'T FOR MY ADELLA?"</i>

492
00:32:00,118 --> 00:32:02,051
SHE WAS YOUR MONA.

493
00:32:03,989 --> 00:32:06,690
[ Sighs ]
JAROD,

494
00:32:06,759 --> 00:32:10,594
<i> YA GOTTA FIND</i>
<i> THAT GIRL FOR MY BOY.</i>

495
00:32:11,663 --> 00:32:13,597
[ Dog Whimpers ]

496
00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:18,167
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>IT SEEMS EVERYBODY WHO MET MONA</i>
<i>WANTED HER:</i>

497
00:32:18,236 --> 00:32:20,904
<i>ARGYLE, HER BROTHER, FALZONE.</i>

498
00:32:20,972 --> 00:32:23,239
<i>IT GOT MY DETECTIVE GEARS</i>
<i>SPINNING.</i>

499
00:32:23,308 --> 00:32:26,910
LOOK, BUDDY BOY. I FOLLOWED
HER HOME ONCE-- OKAY, TWICE.

500
00:32:26,978 --> 00:32:31,381
<i>NICK HAD KNOWN EVERYTHING</i>
<i>ABOUT MONA: WHERE SHE LIVED,</i>
<i>HOW SHE SAVED HER MONEY.</i>

501
00:32:31,450 --> 00:32:33,449
<i>MAYBE HE KNEW</i>
<i>WHO THE FROST BROTHERS WERE.</i>

502
00:32:33,518 --> 00:32:37,186
BUT I SWEAR, I NEVER HEARD
OF THE FROST BROTHERS.
<i>IT WAS ALMOST A DEAD END.</i>

503
00:32:37,255 --> 00:32:39,188
<i>ALMOST.</i>
DIXON.

504
00:32:39,257 --> 00:32:43,226
<i>DEPUTY WYATT HADN'T PUNCHED ME</i>
<i>THE FIRST TIME WE MET.</i>
<i>GUESS HE FIGURED I WAS DUE.</i>

505
00:32:43,295 --> 00:32:47,930
OH, THIS IS GETTIN' REALLY OLD.
YOU TRYIN' TO DESTROY THREE
MONTHS OF REAL POLICE WORK?

506
00:32:47,999 --> 00:32:50,533
WE ALMOST GOT FALZONE
FOR EXTORTION.
SO GET HIM.

507
00:32:50,602 --> 00:32:52,903
AFTER YOU TALKED TO HIM?
YOU OF ALL PEOPLE SHOULD KNOW,

508
00:32:52,972 --> 00:32:55,771
THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY
TO DO THINGS IN THIS TOWN:
THE VEGAS WAY.

509
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:58,375
WHAT ABOUT
THE FROST BROTHERS WAY?

510
00:32:58,443 --> 00:33:00,577
WHAT'S THAT PLACE GOT
TO DO WITH ANYTHING?
PLACE?

511
00:33:00,646 --> 00:33:02,245
PLACE?
PLACE?

512
00:33:02,314 --> 00:33:06,949
PLACE. IT'S AN ABANDONED
MEAT-PACKING PLANT
OUTSIDE TOWN. SO WHAT?

513
00:33:11,122 --> 00:33:14,090
<i>[ Dog Barking, Whimpers ]</i>

514
00:33:17,896 --> 00:33:21,731
MONA?
MONA?

515
00:33:21,800 --> 00:33:24,901
<i> [ Whimpering, Barks ]</i>

516
00:33:25,970 --> 00:33:27,904
MONA?

517
00:33:30,976 --> 00:33:33,877
MONA! MONA!

518
00:33:34,913 --> 00:33:38,448
MONA.
I DIDN'T THINK
YOU'D COME.

519
00:33:38,517 --> 00:33:42,785
OH, YOU'RE SO COLD.
L-LET'S GET YOU OUT OF HERE.
ARGYLE, THESE TWO GUYS--

520
00:33:42,854 --> 00:33:44,855
<i> THEY HAD MASKS ON.</i>
<i> THEY GRABBED ME.</i>

521
00:33:44,923 --> 00:33:47,958
<i> THEY'VE BEEN TRYING</i>
<i> TO GET ME TO TELL THEM</i>
<i> WHAT DIRTY WILLY TOLD ME.</i>

522
00:33:48,026 --> 00:33:51,628
<i> BUT I CAN'T TELL THEM</i>
<i> THAT SECRET, 'CAUSE</i>
<i> I CAN'T DO THAT TO WILLY.</i>

523
00:33:51,697 --> 00:33:54,464
WELL, YOU COULD TELL US
THE SECRET, MONA.
<i>TELL US LATER.</i>

524
00:33:54,533 --> 00:33:56,165
WE HAVE TO GET OUT OF HERE
RIGHT NOW.

525
00:33:56,234 --> 00:33:58,635
YEAH. WE NEED TO GET YOU
BACK TO YOUR BROTHER.

526
00:33:58,704 --> 00:34:01,037
BROTHER?
I DON'T HAVE A BROTHER.

527
00:34:01,106 --> 00:34:04,106
- SURE YOU DO. TWO OF 'EM.
- [ Barks ]

528
00:34:04,175 --> 00:34:08,344
-<i> [ Dog Growling ]</i>
- ARGYLE, SAY HELLO
TO THE FROST BROTHERS.

529
00:34:08,413 --> 00:34:13,149
[ Continues Growling ]

530
00:34:19,891 --> 00:34:22,792
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>IT WAS A CASE TO MAKE</i>
<i>RAY CHANDLER PROUD.</i>

531
00:34:22,861 --> 00:34:26,662
<i>LET'S REVIEW.</i>
<i>OUR TWO SHERIFF DEPUTIES,</i>
<i>WYATT AND MIKE,</i>

532
00:34:26,731 --> 00:34:31,267
<i>THEY KILLED DIRTY WILLY--</i>
<i>TORTURED HIM, FROZE HIM,</i>
<i>HUNG HIM.</i>

533
00:34:31,336 --> 00:34:35,472
<i>BUT WHAT DID THEY WANT</i>
<i>OUT OF HIM? MONEY? DO-RE-MI?</i>

534
00:34:35,540 --> 00:34:38,174
-<i> YOU WON'T BE SURPRISED IF</i>
<i>  I TELL YOU THE ANSWER IS NO.</i>
- [ Whimpers ]

535
00:34:38,243 --> 00:34:41,510
<i>DIRTY WILLY HAD</i>
<i>ONE DIRTY LITTLE SECRET LEFT,</i>

536
00:34:41,579 --> 00:34:45,014
<i>AND THESE GUYS WERE TRYING</i>
<i>TO GET IT OUT OF MONA...</i>
<i>AND US.</i>

537
00:34:45,083 --> 00:34:48,818
- IT'S BEEN EIGHT HOURS.
START TALKING.
- I GOT NOTHIN' TO SAY.

538
00:34:48,887 --> 00:34:52,855
<i>YOU JUST DON'T GET IT,</i>
<i>DO YOU, DIXON?</i>
<i>WE DO THINGS THE VEGAS WAY.</i>

539
00:34:52,924 --> 00:34:56,459
<i>NOW, MONA'S BROTHER HERE IS</i>
<i>GONNA DRIVE HER INTO THE DESERT.</i>

540
00:34:56,528 --> 00:35:01,331
IF HE DOESN'T HEAR
FROM ME IN 30, SHE'S GONE,
AND I ICE THE TWO OF YOU.

541
00:35:03,835 --> 00:35:07,603
- OH, AND I KEEP THE DOG.
- [ Growling Continues ]

542
00:35:07,672 --> 00:35:10,874
DON'T GIVE 'EM ANYTHING, ARGYLE.
NOT ONE QUARTER!

543
00:35:12,644 --> 00:35:15,178
- [ Barking ]
- AH, PUT A SOCK
IN IT, DOG.

544
00:35:15,247 --> 00:35:17,180
THAT WAS
A STRANGE THING
TO SAY.

545
00:35:17,249 --> 00:35:19,749
YEAH, RIGHT--
ESPECIALLY SINCE DOGS
DON'T WEAR SOCKS.

546
00:35:19,817 --> 00:35:23,886
NOT DOG. MONA.
SHE SAID, "NOT A QUARTER."
"DON'T GIVE THEM ONE QUARTER."

547
00:35:23,955 --> 00:35:27,423
WELL, J-MAN, MONA LEFT
A BUCKET FULL OF QUARTERS
IN DICK DIXON'S OFFICE.

548
00:35:27,492 --> 00:35:32,028
DIRTY WILLY'S SECRET. WHATEVER
HE WAS TRYIN' TO PROTECT
MUST HAVE BEEN IN THAT BUCKET.

549
00:35:32,097 --> 00:35:35,364
WYATT!
HEY, WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOIN'?

550
00:35:35,433 --> 00:35:38,535
I'M GONNA GIVE HIM
WHAT HE WANTS. WYATT!

551
00:35:47,178 --> 00:35:50,280
THERE IT IS.
[ Beeps ]

552
00:35:50,348 --> 00:35:52,748
[ Wyatt On Tape ]
LOOK, WILLY.
IF YOU PAY US WHAT WE NEED,

553
00:35:52,818 --> 00:35:55,451
<i> WE WON'T NEED</i>
<i> TO GET ROUGH WITH YOU.</i>
<i> [ Beeps ]</i>

554
00:35:55,520 --> 00:35:58,654
FALZONE WASN'T EXTORTING MONEY
FROM WILLY AND HIS CLUB.
YOU WERE.

555
00:35:58,723 --> 00:36:00,623
AND THE DIRTY FAT BOY
RECORDED ME DOIN' IT.

556
00:36:00,692 --> 00:36:05,095
- ALL THE TIME YOU JUST WANTED
THAT TAPE, IT WAS RIGHT THERE.
- NICE WORK, DETECTIVES.

557
00:36:05,164 --> 00:36:07,497
WILLY WAS JUST TRYIN'
TO GET THAT TAPE
TO DICK DIXON.

558
00:36:07,565 --> 00:36:10,066
SO NOW YOU GOT IT.
CALL YOUR DEPUTY
AND LET MONA GO.

559
00:36:10,134 --> 00:36:13,469
<i>POOR WILLY DIDN'T EVEN KNOW THAT</i>
<i>DICK DIXON HAD SKIPPED TOWN.</i>

560
00:36:13,538 --> 00:36:17,073
WAIT A SECOND.
YOU'RE NOT DICK DIXON?

561
00:36:18,910 --> 00:36:22,278
- NO.
-<i> [ Slot Machine Bell Ringing ]</i>

562
00:36:22,347 --> 00:36:25,648
-<i> [ Ice Pick</i>
<i>    Tapping On Desk ]</i>
- LOSER.

563
00:36:25,717 --> 00:36:28,150
<i>[ Tapping Continues ]</i>

564
00:36:28,219 --> 00:36:30,753
[ Groaning ]

565
00:36:30,822 --> 00:36:32,822
OH, HI, THERE.

566
00:36:33,892 --> 00:36:36,192
LET ME OUTTA THIS.
UH-UH.

567
00:36:36,260 --> 00:36:38,928
- YOU KNOW, YOU SHOULD
BE PROTECTING PEOPLE--
-<i> [ Slot Machine Clicking ]</i>

568
00:36:38,997 --> 00:36:40,930
NOT EXTORTING FROM THEM.

569
00:36:40,999 --> 00:36:43,500
BUT I GUESS
THAT'S WHAT THEY CALL
THE "VEGAS WAY," RIGHT?

570
00:36:43,568 --> 00:36:45,968
- OH, YEAH.
- WELL, WE'VE ALREADY
TRIED THAT.

571
00:36:46,037 --> 00:36:48,271
LET'S TRY THE JAROD WAY.
NO! NO! NO!

572
00:36:49,708 --> 00:36:52,174
- YOU'RE TOTALLY WHACKED.
- YOU DON'T KNOW THE HALF OF IT.

573
00:36:52,243 --> 00:36:56,512
- YOU'RE GOING TO MAKE A CALL.
YOU'RE GOING TO LET MONA GO.
- I DON'T THINK SO.

574
00:36:56,581 --> 00:36:58,647
- LOSER.
- [ Sighs ]

575
00:36:58,716 --> 00:37:01,651
- [ Wyatt Yelps ]
- OH. OOH, THAT'S HARDER
THAN GOLF.

576
00:37:01,719 --> 00:37:03,619
YOU'RE OUTTA YOUR MIND.
MAKE THE CALL.

577
00:37:03,688 --> 00:37:05,488
- NO.
- UH, LOSER.

578
00:37:09,728 --> 00:37:13,295
LAST CHANCE.
[ Breathing Heavily ]

579
00:37:13,364 --> 00:37:16,332
- LOSER.
- OKAY.

580
00:37:18,403 --> 00:37:21,471
- FORE!
-<i> [ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>  WYATT FINALLY MADE THE CALL.</i>

581
00:37:21,539 --> 00:37:25,408
<i>AND SO DID I-- TO THE F.B.I.</i>

582
00:37:25,477 --> 00:37:28,444
<i>WHEN THEY ARRIVED</i>
<i>AT THE OFFICE, THEY FOUND</i>
<i>A KILLER WAITING FOR THEM...</i>

583
00:37:28,513 --> 00:37:30,680
<i>ALONG WITH THE EVIDENCE</i>
<i>TO CONVICT HIM--</i>

584
00:37:30,749 --> 00:37:34,284
<i>ALL COURTESY OF THE MYSTERIOUS</i>
<i>RICHARD W. DIXON.</i>

585
00:37:34,353 --> 00:37:36,285
<i>BUT THE STORY ISN'T OVER.</i>

586
00:37:36,354 --> 00:37:38,821
<i>I STILL HAVE</i>
<i>ONE MORE JOB TO DO.</i>

587
00:37:40,325 --> 00:37:42,692
ANYTHING?

588
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:44,694
NOTHING.

589
00:37:44,763 --> 00:37:49,498
WHICH IS WHAT WE'RE GONNA BE
WHEN WE GET BACK TO THE CENTRE.

590
00:37:49,567 --> 00:37:54,237
IT WAS FUN WHILE IT LASTED--
[ Whispering ]
PUFF DADDY.

591
00:37:57,909 --> 00:38:01,177
<i>[ Faucet Turns, Water Running ]</i>

592
00:38:06,318 --> 00:38:08,284
MISS--

593
00:38:13,124 --> 00:38:17,226
HOO.
I GUESS I'M NOT
A SCRUB ANYMORE.

594
00:38:18,930 --> 00:38:22,799
I HOPE YOU LIKE RENEWAL WING,
'CAUSE I'M GETTIN' YOU
A GIFT CERTIFICATE.

595
00:38:22,868 --> 00:38:26,969
<i> THE CENTRE REEDUCATORS CAN</i>
<i> WIPE THIS ENTIRE WEEKEND</i>
<i> FROM YOUR BRAIN.</i>

596
00:38:27,038 --> 00:38:31,507
<i> [ Jarod ]</i>
<i> WELL, YOU BETTER TELL THEM</i>
<i> THAT BROOTS CAUGHT ME.</i>

597
00:38:34,012 --> 00:38:36,479
[ Chuckles ]

598
00:38:39,317 --> 00:38:43,252
DON'T HAVE TO.
WE'RE A TEAM, AREN'T WE,

599
00:38:43,321 --> 00:38:45,388
DR. FUNKENSTEIN?

600
00:38:45,457 --> 00:38:48,558
<i> WELL, THAT ALL DEPENDS</i>
<i> ON ONE THING, BABY.</i>

601
00:38:48,627 --> 00:38:51,761
<i> AM I YOUR PUFF DADDY?</i>

602
00:38:54,999 --> 00:38:59,302
[ Sighs ]
OH, YEAH, BABY.

603
00:38:59,371 --> 00:39:03,940
<i> AND I WANNA GET FUNKED UP.</i>

604
00:39:06,645 --> 00:39:09,612
OH, I HAVE TO WATCH?

605
00:39:11,115 --> 00:39:13,115
YOU<i> GET</i> TO WATCH.

606
00:39:13,184 --> 00:39:15,451
<i>[ Both Giggle ]</i>

607
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:19,022
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT,
MR. FUNKADELIC.

608
00:39:19,090 --> 00:39:23,159
IF WE'RE GONNA DO THIS,
LET'S DO IT RIGHT.

609
00:39:24,162 --> 00:39:26,462
IT'S MY TURN
TO LIVE OUT A FANTASY.

610
00:39:26,531 --> 00:39:31,701
- BALD MEN HAVE ALWAYS
DRIVEN ME CRAZY.
-<i> [ Broots Chuckles ]</i>

611
00:39:31,769 --> 00:39:36,005
<i>♪ MAKE MY FUNK THE "P" FUNK ♪</i>
AND IT TAKES MORE THAN ONE
TO REALLY SATISFY ME.

612
00:39:36,074 --> 00:39:38,974
- MR. WIGGLES, GET IN HERE!
-<i> ♪♪ [ Continues ]</i>

613
00:39:39,043 --> 00:39:41,244
<i>♪ I WANTS TO GET FUNKED UP ♪</i>
[ Wheels Squeaking ]

614
00:39:41,312 --> 00:39:44,380
<i>♪ I WANT THE BOMB</i>
<i>   I WANT THE "P" FUNK, Y'ALL ♪</i>

615
00:39:44,449 --> 00:39:46,849
<i>♪ DON'T WANT MY FUNK</i>
<i>  STEPPED ON ♪</i>

616
00:39:46,918 --> 00:39:49,652
<i>♪♪ [ Continues ]</i>
MAKE MY FUNK THE "P" FUNK.

617
00:39:49,720 --> 00:39:52,021
<i>[ Man On CD ]</i>
<i>HOME OF</i>
<i>THE EXTRATERRESTRIAL BROTHERS.</i>

618
00:39:52,090 --> 00:39:55,258
<i>♪ MAKE MY FUNK THE "P" FUNK ♪</i>
<i>UNCUT FUNK!</i>

619
00:39:55,327 --> 00:39:58,228
<i> ♪ I WANT MY FUNK UNCUT ♪</i>
<i> "P" FUNK!</i>

620
00:39:58,296 --> 00:40:00,663
- NO.
-<i> ♪♪ [ Continues ]</i>

621
00:40:00,732 --> 00:40:02,698
<i>♪ I WANTS TO GET FUNKED UP ♪♪</i>

622
00:40:02,767 --> 00:40:05,201
MISS PARKER, WHAT ABOUT US?

623
00:40:05,270 --> 00:40:08,237
I WANTS TO GET FUNKED UP.

624
00:40:08,306 --> 00:40:10,640
NO.
<i> ♪♪ [ Continues ]</i>

625
00:40:10,708 --> 00:40:13,008
<i> NO.</i>

626
00:40:13,077 --> 00:40:16,813
NO. NO.

627
00:40:16,882 --> 00:40:19,048
NO!

628
00:40:19,117 --> 00:40:23,652
WHAT THE-- AH! MR. WIGGLES.
[ Sputters ]
OW.

629
00:40:23,721 --> 00:40:26,021
I TOLD YOU NOT TO FALL ASLEEP.

630
00:40:26,090 --> 00:40:28,524
I WAS ASLEEP?
YEAH.

631
00:40:29,594 --> 00:40:32,595
THE WHOLE TIME?
YES, RIP VAN WINKLE.

632
00:40:32,663 --> 00:40:36,165
YOU WERE MAKIN'
SOME WEIRD NOISES TOO.

633
00:40:36,233 --> 00:40:41,004
AND BY THE WAY, WHAT EXACTLY
IS A "PUFF DADDY"?

634
00:40:54,486 --> 00:40:57,820
<i>[ Jarod Narrating ]</i>
<i>LIKE I SAID,</i>
<i>I HAVE ONE MORE THING TO DO.</i>

635
00:40:57,889 --> 00:41:00,957
<i>BUT IT ISN'T THIS... DREAM.</i>

636
00:41:01,025 --> 00:41:03,192
-<i> IT'S SOMEBODY ELSE'S.</i>
- [ Strains ]

637
00:41:08,533 --> 00:41:11,467
- CAN I HELP YOU WITH THAT?
- WHY, I--

638
00:41:12,670 --> 00:41:15,238
[ Chuckling ]
OH, GOD.
OH, GOD.

639
00:41:15,306 --> 00:41:20,910
<i> IF YOU KNEW, SIR, HOW MUCH</i>
<i> I'VE WANTED TO MEET--</i>
<i> THIS IS AN HONOR, SIR.</i>

640
00:41:20,979 --> 00:41:26,115
THIS IS AN HONOR.
LISTEN.
THIRD ROW, POLKA DOT DRESS.

641
00:41:26,184 --> 00:41:28,484
SIR?
ADELLA.

642
00:41:28,553 --> 00:41:32,588
SHE WAS WEARIN'
A POLKA DOT DRESS.
YOU ARE A GOD.

643
00:41:32,656 --> 00:41:38,227
[ Chuckles ]
LISTEN. I UNDERSTAND THERE'S
SOMETHING YOU'D LIKE ME TO HEAR.

644
00:41:38,296 --> 00:41:41,730
- WELL, AS A MATTER OF FACT, UH,
YOU PROBABLY WOULDN'T WANNA--
-<i> ♪♪ [ Accordion: Stray Notes ]</i>

645
00:41:41,799 --> 00:41:43,566
YOU KNOW--
I'D LOVE TO.

646
00:41:43,634 --> 00:41:45,135
YOU WOULD?
I WOULD.

647
00:41:45,203 --> 00:41:47,337
YEAH?
[ Chuckles ]
♪♪ [ Stray Notes ]

648
00:41:47,405 --> 00:41:50,806
OKAY. HERE WE GO.

649
00:41:50,875 --> 00:41:54,744
♪♪ [ Swing Introduction ]

650
00:41:54,812 --> 00:41:57,446
♪ AUF WIEDERSEHEN, BABY ♪

651
00:41:57,515 --> 00:42:01,750
<i> ♪ AUF WIEDERSEHEN ♪</i>

652
00:42:01,820 --> 00:42:04,287
<i> ♪ IT MEANS GOOD-BYE</i>
<i> MY BABY ♪</i>

653
00:42:04,355 --> 00:42:08,090
<i> ♪ I DON'T KNOW WHY</i>
<i>  I FEEL THIS PAIN ♪</i>

654
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:10,493
<i> ♪ IT'S NOT MY GOITER ♪</i>

655
00:42:10,561 --> 00:42:13,696
<i> ♪ BUT LET'S RECONNOITER ♪</i>

656
00:42:13,765 --> 00:42:18,434
<i>♪ SO EVEN THOUGH</i>
<i>  I'M ON THAT FAR-OFF DESERT</i>
<i>  IN MOROCCO ♪</i>

657
00:42:18,503 --> 00:42:21,770
- ♪ I'M FEELIN' ROCKO, BUT
I WANNA DO THIS REFRAIN ♪
- [ Howls ]

658
00:42:21,839 --> 00:42:24,707
<i> ♪ AUF WIEDERSEHEN ♪</i>

659
00:42:24,776 --> 00:42:27,543
-<i> ♪ AUF WIEDERSEHEN ♪♪</i>
- ♪♪ [ Ends ]

660
00:42:27,612 --> 00:42:30,045
- [ Laughing ]
- [ Jarod, Argyle ]
WHOO!

661
00:42:33,384 --> 00:42:35,818
WELL, THAT WAS UNMISTAKABLY YOU.

662
00:42:35,887 --> 00:42:40,023
THAT'S JUST THE FIRST VERSE.
THERE'S MORE TO COME.
I CANNOT WAIT.

663
00:42:40,091 --> 00:42:42,792
UH, LISTEN.
I WANNA SEE YOU ALL
TONIGHT AT MY SHOW.

664
00:42:42,860 --> 00:42:45,661
YOU'LL BE MY GUEST.
I'LL LEAVE YOUR NAMES
AT THE FRONT DOOR.

665
00:42:45,730 --> 00:42:51,467
AND BY THE WAY,
I WANT YOU TO KNOW THAT ADELLA
WAS MY INSPIRATION TOO.

666
00:42:51,535 --> 00:42:55,003
OH, THANK YOU, SIR.
THANK YOU.
SEE YOU. SEE YOU TONIGHT.

667
00:42:56,374 --> 00:42:58,775
[ Benny ]
WHAT A GUY.

668
00:42:58,843 --> 00:43:01,210
THANK YOU.
MY PLEASURE.

669
00:43:01,279 --> 00:43:04,380
THAT COULD BE
THE WORST SONG
I'VE EVER HEARD.

670
00:43:04,449 --> 00:43:08,017
I KNOW. BUT TO HIM IT WAS
A DREAM COME TRUE.
[ Chuckles ]

671
00:43:08,086 --> 00:43:10,019
GUESS THEY MEAN
A LOT TO YOU, HUH?

672
00:43:10,088 --> 00:43:14,089
-<i> HE LISTENED. HE LIKED IT.</i>
- [ Argyle ]
STANDING ROOM ONLY, POP.

673
00:43:14,159 --> 00:43:17,826
SPEAKING OF A LOT,
THANK YOU FOR THAT DONATION.

674
00:43:17,895 --> 00:43:19,828
IT WAS FOR A GOOD CAUSE.

675
00:43:19,898 --> 00:43:22,398
YOU KNOW, I DON'T THINK
I EVER GOT YOUR NAME.

676
00:43:22,467 --> 00:43:25,335
WELL, EVERYONE IN TOWN
CALLS ME DICK DIXON.

677
00:43:25,403 --> 00:43:30,539
YOU'RE DICK DIXON?
YES.

678
00:43:32,176 --> 00:43:34,110
<i>[ Impact ]</i>
<i> [ Body Hitting Ground ]</i>

